descript.abstract: This data layer is a mask covering the San Francisco mainland up to the county line, Treasure Island, and Yerba Buena Island.
descript.purpose: The data layer can be overlaid on other San Francisco layers, so that the layers are clipped at the shoreline. As some city blocks and streets extend out into the ocean and bay, this layer is useful in showing the actual blocks and streets that do not extend out.

procstep.procdesc: Jeff Johnson created a large rectangular polygon shape overlaid over the Shoreline shapefile. Using the Subtract Features command, he subtracted the shoreline shape from the polygon. He did the same with process with the Treasure Island and Yerba Buena Island (part of the sfislands shapefile).
